text.tspan: ... and the Sound of the Baskervilles

flowRoot.flowPara: Two Shades of Blue proudly present a Victorian detective murderÂ­ mystery, with songs!

Holmes and Watson have solved all the crimes in Cornwall, but who knows what dreadful things might happen when detectives get rusty? It seems it is the noble duty of the Baskervilles to provide these poor detectives with more dastardly crimes to solve...

Somebody's got to murder someone and it's nobody's fault. The plot thickens like devious custard as the Baskerville family scheme in all directions, Watson is lured into a bog and the son and heir is sadly decapitated with a chandelier. Featuring lively songs of cunning and intrigue and a romantic proposal at sword point, this is a musical adventure into a world of logic gone mad. With even Watson in danger, will Holmes manage to save the day, helped (or possibly hindered) by incompetent singing policemen?
